We're not as close as you think.
We only share the office.

247
00:21:58,234 --> 00:21:59,861
We have mouths too,
Department Manager Jin.

248
00:22:05,199 --> 00:22:06,826
By the way…

249
00:22:06,909 --> 00:22:09,412
Assistant Manager is out to gather news.

250
00:22:11,372 --> 00:22:15,251
I guess the assistant manager
is busier nowadays.

251
00:22:16,127 --> 00:22:18,463
We're busy too.

252
00:22:19,255 --> 00:22:20,757
You're busy…

253
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:23,468
- Who says we're busy? We're not. Never.
- Some coffee…

254
00:22:23,551 --> 00:22:25,136
- Yeah.
- Han-kyeong, I want coffee.

255
00:22:40,318 --> 00:22:44,238
<i>Jeong-min's getting spicy braised chicken</i>
<i>from a famous spot. Want to join?</i>

256
00:22:45,281 --> 00:22:46,240
<i>I'll make time.</i>

257
00:22:46,324 --> 00:22:48,451
SE-YEONG

258
00:22:56,751 --> 00:22:59,629
Good boy.
Did you call Kyeong-do, Jeong-min?

259
00:22:59,712 --> 00:23:01,964
I did. He's having a team dinner tonight.

260
00:23:02,048 --> 00:23:03,758
What, you…

261
00:23:03,841 --> 00:23:05,259
Why would you tell us now?

262
00:23:05,343 --> 00:23:07,512
Since when did we need Kyeong-do
to gather?

263
00:23:07,595 --> 00:23:08,930
That's not what I mean.

264
00:23:09,013 --> 00:23:12,642
It tastes even better. But even if
he can't make it, we're still Chaos.

265
00:23:12,725 --> 00:23:15,144
What are you talking about?
That's not what I mean.

266
00:23:16,604 --> 00:23:17,855
You see…

267
00:23:19,232 --> 00:23:24,695
I don't think we should spatter our saliva
in front of the chicken made by a master.

268
00:23:24,779 --> 00:23:25,822
You're right.

269
00:23:27,907 --> 00:23:30,618
I should've known better. Let's eat.

270
00:23:30,701 --> 00:23:32,829
Okay, let's eat.

271
00:23:32,912 --> 00:23:33,746
Enjoy.

272
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:36,332
How come you only understand
what Ji-woo says?

273
00:23:36,415 --> 00:23:38,292
Dong-won, is it too spicy?

274
00:23:38,376 --> 00:23:40,253
- Do you want me to rinse it?
- No.

275
00:23:40,336 --> 00:23:41,712
- Hey.
- Dong-won,

276
00:23:41,796 --> 00:23:45,550
you can eat spicy food, and you're here
even when Uncle Kyeong-do is not.

277
00:23:45,633 --> 00:23:47,677
- You'll grow to be a good man.
- Yes!

278
00:23:49,554 --> 00:23:50,805
All right.

279
00:23:50,888 --> 00:23:52,557
Shut up and eat.

280
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:54,267
Just shut up and eat.

281
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:56,769
You're eating a lot.

282
00:23:56,894 --> 00:23:58,771
Have the drumstick and go chirp chirp.

283
00:24:01,482 --> 00:24:03,359
- Be careful. Okay?
- Yeah, bye.

284
00:24:03,442 --> 00:24:06,529
- Bye. Look forward. The stairs.
- Bye.

285
00:24:06,612 --> 00:24:08,447
- Get inside.
- Okay.

286
00:24:08,531 --> 00:24:11,200
- Drive safe. Yeah. Bye.
- Bye!

287
00:24:52,116 --> 00:24:53,910
I sent money to your account.

288
00:24:55,411 --> 00:24:56,245
Money?

289
00:24:56,329 --> 00:24:57,413
I've sent quite a lot.

290
00:24:58,456 --> 00:25:00,708
It'll be enough for you
to live somewhere for a year.

291
00:25:00,791 --> 00:25:02,376
Where would I go?

292
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:06,881
You were going to a university in Chicago,
then you couldn't. Go there.

293
00:25:07,548 --> 00:25:10,259
It would've been nice
that the company covers the cost,

294
00:25:10,343 --> 00:25:12,136
but it'd be meaningful if we send you too.

295
00:25:16,015 --> 00:25:18,351
What? That's so out of the blue.

296
00:25:19,685 --> 00:25:22,813
You kill time at work
when you have nothing to do.

297
00:25:22,897 --> 00:25:25,024
Even when you're home, you don't eat well.

298
00:25:25,566 --> 00:25:27,860
Do you call that a life?

299
00:25:27,944 --> 00:25:29,028
I can take care of myself.

300
00:25:29,111 --> 00:25:31,113
You didn't get any rest.

301
00:25:31,197 --> 00:25:35,034
You took care of me, and helped us here
when we opened the laundromat.

302
00:25:35,952 --> 00:25:38,079
And just when it was getting better…

303
00:25:38,996 --> 00:25:40,581
We're giving you a vacation.

304
00:25:40,665 --> 00:25:46,170
Take a year off,
and go somewhere nice you want to go.

305
00:25:46,254 --> 00:25:49,548
Either study or just have fun.
Get some rest.

306
00:25:59,934 --> 00:26:02,019
I'll think about it.

307
00:26:03,688 --> 00:26:07,066
Besides, I have money. Why are you
giving me your hard-earned money?

308
00:26:07,149 --> 00:26:08,526
Take it.

309
00:26:09,277 --> 00:26:10,987
We're making money for you anyway.

310
00:26:14,782 --> 00:26:15,783
Kyeong-do.

311
00:26:19,370 --> 00:26:20,830
Are you able to carry on?

312
00:26:23,624 --> 00:26:28,587
There are still videos
gossiping about you two.

313
00:26:29,380 --> 00:26:32,466
You two aren't meeting
because you're scared of it.

314
00:26:33,467 --> 00:26:35,886
Not being able to see each other
when you two are so close…

315
00:26:37,555 --> 00:26:38,848
Are you okay with that?

316
00:26:41,767 --> 00:26:43,728
Let me sleep well tonight.

317
00:26:43,811 --> 00:26:47,773
Let me be your parent for once.

318
00:27:09,128 --> 00:27:11,547
- I won't have it then.
- No, please have it.

319
00:27:11,630 --> 00:27:13,466
Can't you read the room?

320
00:28:05,017 --> 00:28:07,478
I was scared when you said
you wanted to see me here.

321
00:28:07,561 --> 00:28:09,772
It's where you said
you wanted to quit before.

322
00:28:09,855 --> 00:28:11,357
I was young back then.

323
00:28:13,859 --> 00:28:16,654
Your mother and father are cool.

324
00:28:19,573 --> 00:28:20,658
I'll accept your leave.

325
00:28:21,617 --> 00:28:23,702
But promise me you'll return.

326
00:28:25,121 --> 00:28:26,122
Thank you.

327
00:28:26,205 --> 00:28:27,206
Jeez.

328
00:28:28,290 --> 00:28:30,209
This is why I don't get in a relationship.

329
00:28:32,002 --> 00:28:34,130
Even if it flops like mine,
it's still worth it.

330
00:28:34,213 --> 00:28:38,050
That's why you should've dated me,
you idiot.

331
00:28:38,134 --> 00:28:40,219
There you go again.

332
00:29:00,781 --> 00:29:03,701
<i>Are you down for lunch?</i>
<i>I'll meet you near your company.</i>

333
00:29:06,787 --> 00:29:08,289
What should I wear?

334
00:29:13,878 --> 00:29:15,546
I'm taking time off from work.

335
00:29:17,214 --> 00:29:18,924
Why? Are you sick?

336
00:29:20,634 --> 00:29:23,554
No, I just want to take a break.

337
00:29:31,312 --> 00:29:33,814
What are you going to do
with your time off?

338
00:29:35,441 --> 00:29:37,401
My mom and dad gave me money.

339
00:29:38,277 --> 00:29:41,155
They told me to go on vacation.
For about a year.

340
00:29:50,039 --> 00:29:51,248
Where are you going?

341
00:29:58,506 --> 00:30:00,966
I have a senior in Cuba.

342
00:30:02,259 --> 00:30:05,137
I'm thinking about going there first.

343
00:30:12,895 --> 00:30:14,063
That's far.

344
00:30:16,232 --> 00:30:17,233
Yeah.

345
00:30:20,152 --> 00:30:21,820
It's far.

346
00:30:28,869 --> 00:30:29,954
Do you need money?

347
00:30:30,704 --> 00:30:32,331
Aren't you short on budget?

348
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:54,061
Promise to tell me when you leave.

349
00:30:55,312 --> 00:30:56,313
Promise…

350
00:30:58,566 --> 00:30:59,692
to tell me.

351
00:31:03,112 --> 00:31:04,113
Okay.

352
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:04,757
Seriously, don't they have
anything else to do?

353
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:06,675
JARIM APPAREL SEO JI-WOO
GIMBAP WITH A FRIEND

354
00:32:06,759 --> 00:32:08,802
Who can ever put up with that?

355
00:32:17,227 --> 00:32:18,646
You can sleep on the plane.

356
00:32:19,521 --> 00:32:20,522
Yes.

357
00:32:22,358 --> 00:32:25,903
I was going to take off with your luggage.
But you checked your bag fast.

358
00:32:28,113 --> 00:32:30,574
Exactly. In case you'd take revenge.

359
00:32:36,121 --> 00:32:37,581
Make sure to eat well.

360
00:32:38,499 --> 00:32:39,750
I'm worried about you.

361
00:32:41,877 --> 00:32:43,295
I didn't cry.

362
00:32:44,463 --> 00:32:47,341
I didn't when you said you were leaving.
I haven't cried since then.

363
00:32:51,887 --> 00:32:54,056
Don't worry about me and have a safe trip.

364
00:32:57,851 --> 00:32:58,852
Okay.

365
00:33:00,854 --> 00:33:01,855
Bye.

366
00:33:02,690 --> 00:33:04,483
Yeah. Bye.

367
00:33:09,113 --> 00:33:10,114
Go on.

368
00:33:32,970 --> 00:33:34,513
Bye. Go on.

369
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:05,103
1 YEAR LATER

370
00:35:05,187 --> 00:35:08,357
Bellinme S/S season is ready.

371
00:35:09,024 --> 00:35:10,526
Thanks to Designer Lucas,

372
00:35:10,609 --> 00:35:15,280
Bellinme will finally be on the gala show
runway early next year in Paris.

373
00:35:19,868 --> 00:35:25,082
And the menswear brand MANZAAR
is improving steadily.

374
00:35:25,165 --> 00:35:28,335
Like a child who almost ran away from home
has turned filial.

375
00:35:30,546 --> 00:35:33,048
Next is our new SPA brand to be launched.

376
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:36,593
I'll have to fly to the head office
in Spain and check.

377
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:41,014
I believe the fabric quality is crucial
for a low-middle-priced brand.

378
00:35:41,098 --> 00:35:43,642
Most people use dryers nowadays.

379
00:35:43,725 --> 00:35:46,478
It's important to make clothes
that don't get damaged,

380
00:35:46,562 --> 00:35:51,024
so we can start by choosing good fabric.

381
00:35:53,944 --> 00:35:54,945
Next…

382
00:35:58,073 --> 00:35:59,908
Lee Kyeong-do must have so much fun.

383
00:36:00,826 --> 00:36:03,704
Once you leave home, it's tough.
How can he be having fun?

384
00:36:05,998 --> 00:36:07,875
Where do you think he is now?

385
00:36:08,834 --> 00:36:11,753
Last time, was it Hokkaido?

386
00:36:11,837 --> 00:36:13,964
Up there in Japan.

387
00:36:15,299 --> 00:36:16,592
See?

388
00:36:16,675 --> 00:36:20,804
He's having fun traveling everywhere.
Mother, you shouldn't have let him go.

389
00:36:21,930 --> 00:36:25,976
It's okay for Kyeong-do to have some fun.
He grew up without puberty crisis.

390
00:36:28,228 --> 00:36:31,940
This is why it's always hard with in-laws.
They only pity their sons.

391
00:36:33,108 --> 00:36:35,402
What are you talking about?

392
00:36:36,737 --> 00:36:37,905
I wish we were in-laws.

393
00:36:38,864 --> 00:36:43,493
Mother, you and I are pretty much
experiencing an in-law fling.

394
00:36:44,453 --> 00:36:46,079
Right, Father?

395
00:36:47,164 --> 00:36:50,834
If you're that curious and annoyed,
call him yourself.

396
00:36:50,918 --> 00:36:52,002
Why are you asking me?

397
00:36:53,462 --> 00:36:54,630
What's wrong about asking you?

398
00:36:54,713 --> 00:36:56,590
Never stop complaining.

399
00:36:58,050 --> 00:37:01,261
You see, I'm being patient.

400
00:37:01,345 --> 00:37:04,222
I'd make an international call
a million times.

401
00:37:05,307 --> 00:37:09,269
But I'm holding back,
so I wouldn't ruin Kyeong-do's effort.

402
00:37:10,771 --> 00:37:12,105
What's he making an effort for?

403
00:37:16,276 --> 00:37:17,361
I don't know.

404
00:37:19,821 --> 00:37:22,699
You probably have a goal.

405
00:37:23,700 --> 00:37:27,204
To rest or to have fun.

406
00:37:27,287 --> 00:37:30,749
Or to study. Something like that.

407
00:37:39,633 --> 00:37:40,926
Whenever I see you…

408
00:37:46,974 --> 00:37:48,266
I just want to be happy.

409
00:37:53,188 --> 00:37:56,858
What's that supposed to mean?

410
00:38:00,070 --> 00:38:01,321
When I go home

411
00:38:02,656 --> 00:38:04,992
after seeing you like this…

412
00:38:08,954 --> 00:38:10,455
I hope to be able to say…

413
00:38:13,125 --> 00:38:14,209
"I'm just glad."

414
00:38:55,667 --> 00:38:56,960
Ta-da.

415
00:39:06,553 --> 00:39:07,554
What are you doing?

416
00:39:09,139 --> 00:39:10,557
My friend said I could try them on.

417
00:39:11,308 --> 00:39:12,726
What's the point of trying that on?

418
00:39:12,809 --> 00:39:13,810
It's a practice.

419
00:39:15,270 --> 00:39:17,898
Why? Are you going to marry another woman?

420
00:39:18,440 --> 00:39:19,274
What?

421
00:39:20,317 --> 00:39:23,111
No, but it's not like
we're getting married now.

422
00:39:23,195 --> 00:39:24,029
This is pretty.

423
00:39:32,079 --> 00:39:34,414
Ta-da.

424
00:39:37,918 --> 00:39:39,002
Let's take a picture.

425
00:39:40,087 --> 00:39:41,922
What? Okay.

426
00:39:43,632 --> 00:39:44,716
Hurry up.

427
00:39:46,551 --> 00:39:47,844
Why are you smiling like that?

428
00:39:47,928 --> 00:39:48,762
What?

429
00:39:50,806 --> 00:39:53,642
Let's try again. One, two, three.

430
00:39:55,268 --> 00:39:57,604
Ji-woo, you look so beautiful.

431
00:39:58,355 --> 00:39:59,189
Let me.

432
00:39:59,272 --> 00:40:00,732
Thanks. Thank you.

433
00:40:01,399 --> 00:40:03,193
Okay, smile.

434
00:40:03,819 --> 00:40:07,405
Ready. One, two, three.

435
00:40:07,489 --> 00:40:08,615
One more?

436
00:40:11,326 --> 00:40:12,577
Okay, smile.

437
00:40:12,661 --> 00:40:15,831
<i>My phone showed this to me</i>
<i>as a souvenir of a few years back.</i>

438
00:40:19,334 --> 00:40:20,335
Isn't it a good picture?

439
00:40:22,087 --> 00:40:25,340
Should I put it somewhere here?
Or should I print more?

440
00:40:25,924 --> 00:40:28,385
I'm this close
to take blood pressure meds.

441
00:40:28,468 --> 00:40:30,887
If you put it here,
my blood pressure will rise.

442
00:40:30,971 --> 00:40:33,348
It's proof that we had an in-laws fling.

443
00:40:33,431 --> 00:40:34,850
I know you like it.

444
00:40:43,441 --> 00:40:44,901
Whatever. I'm leaving that here.

445
00:40:47,612 --> 00:40:49,406
Father, I'll see you later.

446
00:40:49,489 --> 00:40:51,825
- You should stay for dinner.
- Should I?

447
00:40:51,908 --> 00:40:55,412
What are you talking about?
We just had lunch. She has work to do.

448
00:40:55,495 --> 00:40:57,831
I know you're happy to have me here.

449
00:40:58,999 --> 00:41:00,458
- Bye.
- Bye.

450
00:41:00,542 --> 00:41:01,376
I'll come again.

451
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:15,140
Still, she wore the wedding dress
with Kyeong-do first.

452
00:41:16,641 --> 00:41:18,059
Show it to Kyeong-do.

453
00:41:18,143 --> 00:41:20,562
What for? It'd only disturb him.

454
00:41:25,942 --> 00:41:28,612
The show just ended.
Why are you working so hard?

455
00:41:28,695 --> 00:41:31,281
Hey, I have a good feeling
about this play.

456
00:41:31,364 --> 00:41:32,449
What about it?

457
00:41:32,532 --> 00:41:34,201
The lines are easy to memorize,

458
00:41:34,284 --> 00:41:36,661
and the movements are smooth.
How do I say it...

459
00:41:37,662 --> 00:41:38,872
Anyway, it's different.

460
00:41:39,456 --> 00:41:40,790
- Nice.
- It's nice.

461
00:41:40,874 --> 00:41:42,083
- It's nice.
- It is.

462
00:41:48,298 --> 00:41:49,883
Anyway, when is Kyeong-do coming back?

463
00:41:49,966 --> 00:41:50,842
It's been a year.

464
00:41:50,926 --> 00:41:52,510
Is he still wandering?

465
00:41:52,594 --> 00:41:54,179
Kyeong-do did the right thing.

466
00:41:54,262 --> 00:41:56,348
They shouldn't be
on the same latitude and longitude.

467
00:41:56,431 --> 00:41:59,559
As if that could help him get over her,
seriously. Jeez.

468
00:42:01,019 --> 00:42:03,271
- What if that idiot doesn't return?
- Should I go get him?

469
00:42:03,355 --> 00:42:06,733
Yeah, you should go get him. Gosh.

470
00:42:09,402 --> 00:42:10,987
Where do you think he is?

471
00:42:12,697 --> 00:42:13,782
I miss him.

472
00:42:53,405 --> 00:42:55,615
- Oh, really?
- Yep.

473
00:44:50,313 --> 00:44:53,608
ECOLOGICAL LAUNDRY

474
00:45:51,040 --> 00:45:52,417
Why did you want to see me?

475
00:45:53,626 --> 00:45:58,131
Ro-a's school has a long break.
I'll be there for a while.

476
00:45:59,007 --> 00:46:01,426
You should come straight to New York
from Barcelona.

477
00:46:02,343 --> 00:46:03,845
Ro-a says she misses her aunt.

478
00:46:04,721 --> 00:46:07,015
Just go and enjoy mother-daughter time.

479
00:46:12,854 --> 00:46:14,022
Here.

480
00:46:14,606 --> 00:46:15,523
What's this?

481
00:46:15,607 --> 00:46:19,444
You might need your dopamine recharged
before going faraway to work.

482
00:46:22,405 --> 00:46:24,449
Let me see…

483
00:46:33,333 --> 00:46:36,794
Seo Ji-yeon. You have a taste.

484
00:46:36,878 --> 00:46:40,423
So let's have fun in New York
with your sister who has a taste.

485
00:46:43,384 --> 00:46:47,931
I'll use this every day. I love it.
No way you picked this on your own.

486
00:46:48,014 --> 00:46:51,309
- Who was it? Who? It wasn't you.
- I don't like you anymore.

487
00:46:51,392 --> 00:46:52,685
Yeah, it was Secretary Cha.

488
00:47:03,530 --> 00:47:05,365
Don't worry about me and have a safe trip.

489
00:47:08,034 --> 00:47:09,035
Okay.

490
00:47:11,037 --> 00:47:12,038
Bye.

491
00:47:15,083 --> 00:47:16,084
Director Seo.

492
00:47:17,794 --> 00:47:18,836
Did you arrive early?

493
00:47:18,920 --> 00:47:20,547
I just got here.

494
00:47:20,630 --> 00:47:21,839
- Shall we go?
- Yes.

495
00:47:28,346 --> 00:47:31,683
BARCELONA

496
00:48:24,902 --> 00:48:28,740
Hey, Ji-yeon. Is Ro-a having fun?

497
00:48:29,657 --> 00:48:30,658
Nice.

498
00:48:32,285 --> 00:48:34,412
The team manager and everyone
left already.

499
00:48:35,079 --> 00:48:36,080
Yeah.

500
00:48:37,373 --> 00:48:41,377
Well… I plan to stay here
for a few more days.

501
00:48:43,296 --> 00:48:45,673
Me? I have so many places to go.

502
00:48:46,341 --> 00:48:48,926
I plan to fly to England
and meet Daniel before I go.

