543
01:00:29,001 --> 01:00:30,002
So-so.

544
01:00:39,720 --> 01:00:42,014
Is Dong-won sleeping?

545
01:00:42,097 --> 01:00:43,098
Yes.

546
01:00:59,698 --> 01:01:02,159
When our parents met before the wedding,

547
01:01:03,369 --> 01:01:06,205
my dad kept apologizing.

548
01:01:06,288 --> 01:01:08,123
It offended me.

549
01:01:10,334 --> 01:01:13,212
I was probably upset
because I felt guilty.

550
01:01:14,338 --> 01:01:16,715
You know how capricious I am.

551
01:01:19,051 --> 01:01:23,931
No matter how much I think about it,

552
01:01:26,100 --> 01:01:29,228
I don't have any memories
of hating Woo-sik.

553
01:01:32,564 --> 01:01:34,900
He really did everything the way I wanted.

554
01:01:38,487 --> 01:01:40,614
My dad was right.

555
01:01:42,199 --> 01:01:43,534
I feel bad for him.

556
01:01:46,662 --> 01:01:48,455
But you were good to him too.

557
01:01:48,539 --> 01:01:49,998
Right.

558
01:01:50,624 --> 01:01:53,710
Woo-sik didn't make a lot of money
from his acting jobs.

559
01:01:54,336 --> 01:01:56,422
He was thankful
that you never nagged at him.

560
01:01:58,298 --> 01:02:00,467
I thought about Woo-sik on my way here.

561
01:02:02,177 --> 01:02:05,347
I'm glad he got
to perform Waiting for Godot.

562
01:02:07,266 --> 01:02:09,309
Like a fool, I thought about that.

563
01:02:51,268 --> 01:02:53,437
FOREVER FRIEND
LATE CHA WOO-SIK RESTS HERE FOREVER

564
01:03:17,544 --> 01:03:18,921
Where are you staying these days?

565
01:03:27,387 --> 01:03:29,932
I actually went to Málaga.

566
01:03:31,808 --> 01:03:34,853
After a business trip to Barcelona.

567
01:03:36,146 --> 01:03:37,981
The flea market was still there.

568
01:03:41,401 --> 01:03:42,402
Ji-woo.

569
01:03:47,241 --> 01:03:49,451
Those times
when you left far away from me...

570
01:03:51,828 --> 01:03:53,497
I thought a lot...

571
01:03:55,415 --> 01:03:59,169
about how much it must've been painful
to you during those times.

572
01:04:06,218 --> 01:04:10,847
When you were left here,
your days must've been hollow.

573
01:04:12,849 --> 01:04:15,102
That's what I thought too.

574
01:04:23,110 --> 01:04:24,319
Are you going back?

575
01:04:28,490 --> 01:04:30,492
Well, I left in a rush.

576
01:04:35,455 --> 01:04:36,456
When?

577
01:04:37,833 --> 01:04:40,836
After I take my dad to the hospital
for his medical checkup,

578
01:04:42,129 --> 01:04:43,130
I'm leaving.

579
01:04:46,508 --> 01:04:49,678
Right. You should leave.

580
01:06:37,369 --> 01:06:41,248
<i>I keep thinking if I'm a kind man.</i>

581
01:06:51,174 --> 01:06:56,388
<i>Some wise man said</i>
<i>that one's kindness eventually pays off.</i>

582
01:07:03,687 --> 01:07:05,897
Mother, what time is Kyeong-do's flight?

583
01:07:05,981 --> 01:07:07,065
What?

584
01:07:11,278 --> 01:07:13,280
You should've called earlier.

585
01:07:13,363 --> 01:07:16,533
Don't talk. Focus on driving.
If I miss him, it's your fault.

586
01:07:16,616 --> 01:07:18,994
What if you catch him?
Will you make him stay this time?

587
01:07:19,077 --> 01:07:21,580
Say it right now.
Just live together already!

588
01:07:21,663 --> 01:07:22,956
Drive faster!

589
01:07:23,039 --> 01:07:24,124
Damn it.

590
01:07:26,793 --> 01:07:32,090
<i>If you have memories</i>
<i>of me being kind, and…</i>

591
01:07:33,759 --> 01:07:37,179
<i>if life sends you to me for one last time…</i>

592
01:07:41,349 --> 01:07:43,351
<i>May I have your attention, please?</i>

593
01:07:44,519 --> 01:07:45,896
Lee Kyeong-do!

594
01:07:51,860 --> 01:07:52,986
Kyeong-do.

595
01:08:01,411 --> 01:08:02,579
Don't go.

596
01:08:05,415 --> 01:08:06,625
I…

597
01:08:06,708 --> 01:08:08,794
I don't mind.

598
01:08:10,253 --> 01:08:12,255
I don't mind at all. I...

599
01:08:12,923 --> 01:08:14,800
I'm fine with the adulteress stigma.

600
01:08:17,135 --> 01:08:18,887
It doesn't upset me at all.

601
01:08:20,347 --> 01:08:22,766
But living without you upsets me the most.

602
01:08:28,730 --> 01:08:30,774
You're the only one I like.

603
01:08:32,567 --> 01:08:36,363
As long as I have you, I don't mind
the slimy sink in Yeonnam-dong.

604
01:08:38,406 --> 01:08:41,326
Just... Just one thing.

605
01:08:42,452 --> 01:08:43,453
You.

606
01:08:45,372 --> 01:08:46,873
You're the only one I like.

607
01:09:03,557 --> 01:09:04,808
It's heavy.

608
01:09:06,518 --> 01:09:07,519
No.

609
01:09:09,521 --> 01:09:10,355
You can't go.

610
01:09:45,390 --> 01:09:46,391
Let's go.

611
01:09:49,436 --> 01:09:50,645
Let's go home.

612
01:09:52,731 --> 01:09:53,732
Let's go…

613
01:09:58,820 --> 01:09:59,821
and live together.

614
01:10:31,353 --> 01:10:32,604
<i>In the end,</i>

615
01:10:34,064 --> 01:10:35,065
<i>I surrender...</i>

616
01:10:37,400 --> 01:10:38,234
<i>to our time.</i>

617
01:11:29,160 --> 01:11:32,414
You and I probably have healthy livers,
right?

618
01:11:32,497 --> 01:11:33,581
I guess so?

619
01:11:35,583 --> 01:11:38,294
We don't drink. We don't smoke.

620
01:11:38,378 --> 01:11:40,380
We must be in excellent shape.

621
01:11:42,215 --> 01:11:46,428
I had a medical checkup. I'm no joke.
They say I'm like in my 20s.

622
01:11:52,100 --> 01:11:54,060
People can be very cunning.

623
01:12:03,028 --> 01:12:04,612
This coffee smells nice.

624
01:12:06,239 --> 01:12:08,992
I thought I wouldn't need anything
as long as I had you.

625
01:12:09,492 --> 01:12:11,411
And that is still true, but…

626
01:12:12,912 --> 01:12:17,042
The thing about greed is…

627
01:12:19,044 --> 01:12:20,420
Look, Lee Kyeong-do.

628
01:12:21,212 --> 01:12:23,089
We're in our best shape.

629
01:12:24,215 --> 01:12:25,216
Yeah.

630
01:12:25,800 --> 01:12:27,135
Then what should we do?

631
01:12:34,976 --> 01:12:36,102
Uh, exercise?

632
01:12:40,690 --> 01:12:41,691
We should have a baby.

633
01:12:42,358 --> 01:12:43,193
What?

634
01:12:44,152 --> 01:12:46,279
Let's have a baby
who looks like you and me.

635
01:12:47,030 --> 01:12:49,866
I'm already of advanced maternal age.
We need to rush.

636
01:12:49,949 --> 01:12:53,411
Hey, Ji-woo.
We need to discuss in depth and plan--

637
01:12:53,495 --> 01:12:55,246
Are you scared that they'd take after me?

638
01:12:57,624 --> 01:12:58,666
That too.

639
01:13:01,503 --> 01:13:02,754
Let's go.

640
01:13:02,837 --> 01:13:03,880
Go where?

641
01:13:04,839 --> 01:13:07,550
I said, we don't have much time.
Let's have a baby.

642
01:13:09,094 --> 01:13:10,637
- Where to?
- Your house.

643
01:13:11,304 --> 01:13:13,306
That place has good energy. Let's go.

644
01:13:14,933 --> 01:13:17,227
Hey, wait. But it's broad daylight.

645
01:13:17,310 --> 01:13:19,229
Seriously. Stop complaining and follow me.

646
01:13:20,105 --> 01:13:22,941
No. Wait, this is baffling.

647
01:13:23,024 --> 01:13:28,196
Come on. This is all a natural process.
We should get it started.

648
01:13:28,988 --> 01:13:30,490
What? Start what?

649
01:13:30,573 --> 01:13:35,620
THANK YOU FOR WATCHING <i>SURELY TOMORROW.</i>
